data:
Tumor size and grade are important factors in determining the cancer stage, but do not directly contribute to the N stage.
The N stage is determined by the number of positive axillary lymph nodes.
N0: No positive axillary lymph nodes.
N1: Metastasis in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes.
N2: Metastasis in 4-9 axillary lymph nodes.
N3: Metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes.

The N stage does not consider the total number of lymph nodes removed, only the number that are positive for metastasis.
